nes interview and participant-observation material gathered over the course of two years in the community, Cassaniti shows how Buddhist ideas are understood, interrelated, and reinforced through secular and religious practices in everyday life. She compares the emotional experiences of Buddhist villagers with religious and cultural practices in a nearby Christian village. Living Buddhism highlights the importance of change, calmness (as captured in the Thai phrase jai yen, or a cool heart), and karma; Cassaniti's narrative untangles the Thai villagers' feelings and problems and the solutions they seek.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aBuddhismzThailandzChiang Mai. 0aHealthxReligious aspectsxBuddhism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501700989423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9781501700989.jpg  a978-3-11-066749-3  COR eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles